# Door & Window Variants

## Context

Doors and windows are fully implemented with a single type each: swing doors and standard (three-line) windows. This plan adds variant types â€” double and sliding doors, casement and fixed windows â€” so the user can place a default type and then change it via the properties panel.

## Design Decisions

- **Type selection happens after placement** â€” the user places a door/window with defaults, then changes type in the properties panel. No new toolbar buttons or placement handlers needed.
- **One new field per model**: `door.type` (`'swing'`|`'double'`|`'sliding'`) and `win.type` (`'standard'`|`'casement'`|`'fixed'`). Windows also gain `openDirection` (for casement).
- **Rendering branches inside existing renderers** â€” extract variant-specific SVG into helper components, keep the wall-masking polygon shared.
- **No new constants or geometry helpers** â€” all variants reuse the same `doorOutlineOnWall`/`windowOutlineOnWall` positioning.

