## Change 4: Window variant rendering in `WindowRenderer.jsx`

Refactor similarly. Masking polygon stays the same.

**`standard` (default, current code unchanged):**
- Three parallel lines at perpendicular offsets -0.3, 0, +0.3

**`casement` (new):**
- Uses a `<g transform="translate/rotate">` like doors (at `info.start`, rotated by angle)
- Glass pane line: `(0,0)` â†’ `(win.width, 0)`, strokeWidth 2
- Hinge leaf: short line from `(0,0)` â†’ `(0, flipSign * -win.width * 0.3)`
- Small dashed arc: radius `win.width * 0.3`, quarter-circle from pane to leaf end
- `flipSign` from `win.openDirection`

**`fixed` (new):**
- Center line from `info.start` â†’ `info.end`, strokeWidth 2
- Two diagonal lines forming an X: `info.p1â†’info.p3` and `info.p2â†’info.p4`, strokeWidth 1

